File and Directory Operations:
os.getcwd(): Get the current working directory.
os.chdir(path): Change the current working directory to path.
os.listdir(path='.'): Return a list of the entries in the directory given by path.
os.mkdir(path): Create a directory named path.
os.makedirs(path): Recursive directory creation function.
File and Directory Information:
os.stat(path): Get the status of a file or a file descriptor.
os.path.exists(path): Check whether the path exists.
os.path.isfile(path): Check whether the path is a regular file.
os.path.isdir(path): Check whether the path is a directory.
os.path.basename(path): Get the base name of the path.
os.path.dirname(path): Get the directory name of the path.
Process Management:
os.system(command): Execute the command in a subshell.
os.spawnv(mode, path, args): Execute the program path in a new process.
os.fork(): Fork a child process.
os.waitpid(pid, options): Wait for a child process to terminate.
Environment Variables:
os.getenv(key, default=None): Get the value of the environment variable named key.
os.putenv(key, value): Set the value of the environment variable key to value.
os.environ: A mapping object representing the current environment variables.
File Descriptor Operations:
os.open(file, flags[, mode]): Open a file (similar to open() but returns a file descriptor).
os.close(fd): Close a file descriptor.
os.read(fd, buffersize): Read data from the file descriptor.
os.write(fd, data): Write data to the file descriptor.
